    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001318_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><opener><add place="above" hand="#U">52</add> <add rend="diagonal" hand="#U"><unclear cert="medium"><persName>Moffat</persName> &amp; <gap extent="1" unit="words"/></unclear></add> <dateline rend="right"><placeName>Steamer Pearl</placeName> <add place="margintop" hand="#U">100</add><date when="1858-05-07">7th May
<lb/> 1858</date></dateline>
<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>My Dear Tom</salute></opener>

<lb/><p><persName>Mama</persName> was so
<lb/>sick all the way from
<lb/><placeName><country>Sierra Leone</country></placeName> to the <unclear cert="low">lake</unclear>
<lb/>that I was obliged to leave
<lb/>her and <persName>Oswell</persName> there. 
<lb/>But <persName><choice><sic>Grand Pa</sic><corr>Grandpa</corr></choice> &amp; Grandma
<lb/>Moffat</persName> were there on a 
<lb/>visit to <placeName><settlement type="city">Cape Town</settlement></placeName> and
<lb/>happily were ready to 
<lb/>take charge of Mama up to 

	<pb facs="liv_001318_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="town">Kuruman</settlement></placeName> whither she will
<lb/>now go while I am sailing
<lb/>along the <unclear cert="low">north east</unclear> to 
<lb/>the <placeName><geogName type="river">Zambezi</geogName></placeName>. We hope to
<lb/>meet <persName>Mama</persName> &amp; <persName>Oswell</persName>
<lb/>when she is better but we
<lb/>shall be parted a year at
<lb/>least - <persName>Gandpa</persName> has been 
<lb/>to see <persName><unclear cert="low">Mosch katze</unclear></persName> and 
<lb/>finds him willing to recieve 
<lb/>a teacher - <persName>Uncle John</persName>
<lb/>may possibly go and live
<lb/>with him to instruct him
<lb/>in the way of life - but that
<lb/>is not yet certain - I hope
<lb/>you are <choice><sic>recieving</sic><corr>receiving</corr></choice> into your

	<pb facs="liv_001318_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>heart the knowledge of <persName>Jesus</persName>
<lb/>and that you feel him to
<lb/>be your saviour and friend
<lb/>Tell him all your wants
<lb/>and cares for he cares for 
<lb/>the humblest of the sons
<lb/>of men, and he loves all
<lb/>and watches over all.</p>
<lb/><p>I hope you are getting
<lb/>on with your lessons at
<lb/>school and becoming fitted
<lb/>to be something and of some
<lb/>use to your dear saviour
<lb/>in the world - You must
<lb/>live for him - give yourself
<lb/>up to him to be saved and

	<pb facs="liv_001318_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>sanctified by him and you
<lb/>will be complete for ever
<lb/>in him. Write to Agnes
<lb/>&amp; Robert.</p>
<lb/><p>Don't be content to crawl
<lb/>through with your lessons
<lb/>you must walk on with
<lb/>them - try to be first - <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> 
<lb/>Young</persName> will arrange for 
<lb/>another school when it is 
<lb/>necessary and wherever 
<lb/>you are look up with a
<lb/>loving heart to him who
<lb/>tenderly regards both man
<lb/>and bird &amp; beast - </p><closer><salute>I am &amp;</salute><!-- Change as appropriate -->
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer><!-- Change as appropriate --> 

<lb/><postscript><p rend="no-indent">My kind regards to <persName>Dr. Landon</persName> 
<lb/><space extent="5" unit="chars"/>&amp; his son</p></postscript>

            </div>
